'''-{zh-tw:傑瑞米·杭特;zh-hk:侯俊偉;zh-cn:杰里米·理查德·斯特雷恩沙姆·亨特}-'''（{{lang-en|Jeremy Richard Streynsham Hunt}}-{zh-cn:，港澳[[英國官方與政治人物漢化譯名列表|汉化译名]]'''侯俊伟'''，; zh-hk:，; zh-tw:，港澳[[英國官方與政治人物漢化譯名列表|漢化譯名]]'''侯俊偉'''，}-{{bd|1966年|11月1日||catIdx=Hunt, Jeremy}}），[[英国保守党|英国保守党]]政治家。[[2005年英国大选|2005年]]當選[[西南薩里_(英國國會選區)|西南薩里]]议员。<ref>{{Cite web|title=BBC Radio 4 - Profile, Jeremy Hunt|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01gngrd|accessdate=4 April 2019|website=BBC|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111222218/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01gngrd|dead-url=no}}</ref>曾任文化大臣、卫生大臣、[[外交及聯邦事務大臣|外交及聯邦事務大臣]]。亨特自稱认可[[一国保守主义|一国保守主义]]，被认为支持[[经济自由主义|经济自由主义]]和[[社会自由主义|社会自由主义]]政策。

亨特生于伦敦[[肯宁顿|肯宁顿]]，于[[牛津大学莫德林学院|牛津大学莫德林学院]]研习[[哲学、政治学及经济学|哲学、政治学及经济学]]，曾任{{le|牛津大学保守协会主席|Oxford University Conservative Association}}。[[2005年英国大选|2005年]]當選[[西南薩里_(英國國會選區)|西南薩里]]议员，在影子内阁升任[[残疾人影子部长|残疾人影子部长]]，后来改任为[[文化、媒体和体育影子影子内阁国务大臣|文化、媒体和体育影子影子内阁国务大臣]]。

2010年到2012年任文化大臣（2010-2012），任职期间，亨特致力于发展地方电视台，使[[通讯管理局|通讯管理局]]颁发执照给地方自治市镇的小电视台。亨特还监督了[[2012年伦敦奥运会|2012年伦敦奥运会]]，受到了广泛赞誉。

2012年到2018年任卫生大臣（2012-2018），2018年1月，改卫生和社會保障大臣。卫生大臣任上，亨特与{{le|初级医生|junior doctors}}谈判并修改了合同，使得他们的基本工资上涨，但他们的保险期被缩短，星期六也变成了工作日。与医生工会[[英国医学会|英国医学会]]（BMA）的谈判失败，导致2016年多次罢工。[[英国医学杂志|英国医学杂志]]的编辑和BMA理事会主席，指责亨特歪曲研究成果以支持自己的行动，即全国医疗服务在周末缺乏人手导致了一些本可避免的医疗事故。2018年6月，他成为英国政治史上在职时间最长的卫生大臣。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/politics/jeremy-hunt-longest-serving-health-12637749|title=Jeremy Hunt's calamitous 2,099-day reign by numbers as he becomes UK's longest-serving Health Secretary|work=Daily Mirror|accessdate=5 June 2018|archive-date=2021-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125200507/https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/politics/jeremy-hunt-longest-serving-health-12637749|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2018年7月，[[约翰逊|约翰逊]]辞职后接任外交大臣，直至2019年7月[[约翰逊|约翰逊]]成為首相。

== 早年生活和教育 ==
亨特生于肯宁顿的贝兰斯医院，<ref>{{cite news |work=[[The_Times|The Times]]|date=1966-11-02|page=2|title=Births}}</ref>是时任[[英国国防部|国防部]]海军项目主任<ref>{{cite news |work=The Times|date=1966-05-09|page=14|title=Appointments in the Forces|trans_title=在部队的约会}}</ref>{{le|尼古拉斯·亨特|Nicholas Hunt}}<ref name="bbca">{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-17822923 |title=Profile: Jeremy Hunt – BBC News |trans_title=杰里米·亨特简介 |publisher=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |date=2012-05-31 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2018-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924183752/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-17822923 |dead-url=no }}</ref>海军中校的长子。尼古拉斯·亨特后来官至[[北约|北约]]{{le|大西洋盟军司令部最高指挥官|Supreme Allied Commander Atlantic}}，授海军上将军衔。杰里米·亨特的母亲Meriel Givan则是陆军少校亨利·吉文的女儿。<ref>{{cite news |work=The Times|date=1965-09-23|page=1|title=Forthcoming marriages|trans_title=即将结婚}}</ref>亨特也是[[不列颠东印度公司|不列颠东印度公司]]创立者之一Streynsham Master的后人。<ref>Burke's Peerage, Baronetage and Knightage, 2003, vol. 3, p. 3285</ref>

亨特在[[萨里郡|萨里郡]]的[[舍尔|舍尔]]长大，那里后来成为其国会[[选区|选区]]。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.surreylife.co.uk/out-about/places/jeremy_hunt_opens_radisson_edwardian_guildford_8211_and_shares_hotel_tipping_advice_1_1647952|title=Jeremy Hunt opens Radisson Edwardian Guildford – and shares hotel tipping advice... – Places – Surrey|trans_title=亨特参加酒店庆典并分享拿小费的经验|work=Surrey Life|date=2011-11-03|accessdate=2015-07-27|archive-date=2016-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221044924/http://www.surreylife.co.uk/out-about/places/jeremy_hunt_opens_radisson_edwardian_guildford_8211_and_shares_hotel_tipping_advice_1_1647952|dead-url=no}}</ref>他是[[伊丽莎白二世|伊丽莎白二世女王]]和英国法西斯联盟创始人[[奥斯瓦尔德·莫斯利|奥斯瓦尔德·莫斯利]]的远亲。<ref>{{cite news |first=Juliette |last=Jowit |first2=Shiv |last2=Malik |first3=Haroon |last3=Siddique |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/sep/04/new-cabinet |title=Cabinet reshuffle: who has moved so far? | Politics |trans_title=内阁改组：谁被调动？ |work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |date=2012-09-04 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2020-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926042635/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/sep/04/new-cabinet |dead-url=no }}</ref>

他[[查特豪斯公學|查特豪斯公學]]接受了早期教育，是{{le|男生代表|Head girl and head boy}}。<ref name="bbca"/>后在[[牛津大学莫德林学院|牛津大学莫德林学院]]学习[[哲学、政治学及经济学|哲学、政治学及经济学]]，并以{{le|一等荣誉文学士|first class honours}}学位毕业。在牛津他开始接触保守党政治，[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]、[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]均是他的同学。<ref name="Walker">Tim Walker [http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/jeremy-hunt-rough-ride-for-the-smooth-operator-2017277.html "Jeremy Hunt: Rough ride for the smooth operator"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/jeremy-hunt-rough-ride-for-the-smooth-operator-2017277.html |date=20190809085450 }}, ''The Independent'', 3 July 2010</ref>他活跃于牛津大学保守协会（OUCA），并于1987年当选为主席。<ref name="Walker" />

== 早期事业 ==
大学毕业后他曾在欧析企业管理咨询公司做了两年的管理顾问，后来去日本当[[英语|英语]]老师，学会了日语，并对东方文化产生了兴趣。<ref name=mediaweek>{{cite news |last=Dennys |first=Harriet |url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/918321/hunt-lays-down-tory-blueprint-media?src_site=mediaweek |title=Hunt lays down Tory blueprint for media – Media news |trans_title=亨特为媒体打下了保守党的蓝图 |work=Media Week |date=2009-07-07 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2016-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001201329/http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/918321/hunt-lays-down-tory-blueprint-media?src_site=mediaweek |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在他回到英国后，又在一些不同的创业企业中尝试过，<ref name="auto">{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ill-make-a-brexit-deal-because-business-is-my-bread-and-butter-says-jeremy-hunt-drg883zpj|title=I’ll make a Brexit deal because business is my bread and butter, says Jeremy Hunt|first=Tim|last=Shipman|work=The Sunday Times|date=25 May 2019|accessdate=5 June 2019|archive-date=2021-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113120743/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ill-make-a-brexit-deal-because-business-is-my-bread-and-butter-says-jeremy-hunt-drg883zpj|dead-url=no}}</ref>包括向日本出口果酱，但不成功。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jeremyhunt.org/newsshow.aspx?ref=452|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091030143251/http://www.jeremyhunt.org/newsshow.aspx?ref=452|title=Broadcast magazine interview with|trans_title=广播杂志采访|website=jeremyhunt.org|archivedate=2009-10-30|deadurl=yes}}</ref> 1991年，亨特与一位儿时朋友Mike Elms合作创立了名为Profile PR的[[公关|公关]]公司，专门从事[[IT|IT]]公关业务。<ref name=mediaweek/>亨特和Elms后来出售了Profile PR公司，专注于出版工商目录。

亨特一直有志“指导、帮助那些想要学习而不仅仅是出国旅行的人”，<ref name="szdaily.com">{{cite web|title=Jeremy Hunt: Japanese-speaking 'great survivor' once pro-EU|url=http://www.szdaily.com/content/2018-07/13/content_21043785.htm|accessdate=17 January 2019|date=|work=Szdaily.com|archive-date=2019-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626182954/http://www.szdaily.com/content/2018-07/13/content_21043785.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>20世纪90年代，亨特和Elms成立了一家名为{{le|热门|Hotcourses}}的教育公司，该司目前也是全世界最大的课程数据库，其中一个主要客户是[[英国文化协会|英国文化协会]]。<ref name="Hotcourses" />亨特在2009年成为公司董事，但仍然保留了48％的公司股份，这些股份是保密委托的，在2017年1月之前热门公司售出超过价值3000万英镑的澳大利亚教育组织{{le|澳大利亚教育国际开发署|IDP Education}}（IDP）股票。亨特从中获得了超过1400万英镑。<ref name="Hotcourses">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jan/16/jeremy-hunt-in-line-for-145m-windfall-over-hotcourses-sale|title=Jeremy Hunt in line for £14.5m windfall over Hotcourses sale|trans_title=杰里米·亨特在热门公司的资产管理中获利1450万英镑|work=The Guardian|date=2017-01-16|last=Walker|first=Peter|accessdate=2017-01-17|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202025422/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jan/16/jeremy-hunt-in-line-for-145m-windfall-over-hotcourses-sale|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-38638577|title=Hunt makes millions from sale of Hotcourses|trans_title=亨特获利数百万英镑|publisher=BBC News|date=2017-01-16|last=Pollock|first=Ian|access-date=2017-01-17|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111210251/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-38638577|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=The NS Profile "The Last Cameroon: Jeremy Hunt is on a mission to unite his fractured party - and the country"|url=|last=Cowley|first=Jason|date=18 April – 2 May 2019|journal=New Statesman|volume=|pages=24–33|via=}}</ref>

== 国会议员 ==
[[2005年英国大选|2005年]]他在[[西南萨里_(英国国会选区)|西南萨里]]选区当选国会议员，他的前任{{le|维多利亚·波特姆利|Virginia Bottomley}}因获封[[终身贵族|终身贵族]]而离任，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1946855/Conservatives-The-50-most-influential-figures-on-the-new-Right.html|title=Conservatives: The 50 most influential figures on the new Right|trans_title=保守党：新右派中最有影响力的50人|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=2008-05-11|last=Winnett|first=Robert|accessdate=2017-02-08|archive-date=2019-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623115635/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1946855/Conservatives-The-50-most-influential-figures-on-the-new-Right.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.uk/biographies/lords/baroness-bottomley-of-nettlestone/106|title=Baroness Bottomley of Nettlestone|trans_title=内特尔斯通的波特姆利女男爵|publisher=parliament.uk|accessdate=2016-09-30|archive-date=2019-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822082807/https://www.parliament.uk/biographies/lords/baroness-bottomley-of-nettlestone/106|dead-url=no}}</ref>亨特的多数票为5711张。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/election-2010/7635381/General-Election-2010-top-Labour-Tory-and-Liberal-Democrat-MPs-who-could-lose-seats.html|title=General Election 2010: top Labour, Tory and Liberal Democrat MPs who could lose seats|trans_title=2010年大选：工党、保守党和自民党的议员们谁会失去议席？|work=[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]|date=2010-04-26|accessdate=2016-02-24|archive-date=2019-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725135707/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/election-2010/7635381/General-Election-2010-top-Labour-Tory-and-Liberal-Democrat-MPs-who-could-lose-seats.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2005年[[英国保守党领袖|英国保守党领袖]]选举，亨特支持卡梅伦，2005年12月被卡梅伦任命为影子残障人士副大臣。同年，他与人合著《直接民主：新模范党议程》政策小册子，其中声明支持[[國民健康署|國民健康署]]的非国有化，并建议将其替换为“全民保险”。亨特后来不再坚持这样的观点。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jeremy-hunt-privatise-nhs-tories-privatising-private-insurance-market-replacement-direct-democracy-a6865306.html|title=Jeremy Hunt co-authored book calling for NHS to be replaced with private insurance|trans_title=杰里米·亨特著书呼吁以私人医保代替公立医保|work=The Independent|date=2016-02-10|last=Stone|first=Jon|accessdate=2017-02-08|archive-date=2021-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313072938/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/jeremy-hunt-privatise-nhs-tories-privatising-private-insurance-market-replacement-direct-democracy-a6865306.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2007年7月2日，卡梅伦改组[[影子内阁|影子内阁]]，亨特昇任影子文化、媒體及體育大臣。[[2010年英国大选|2010年大选]]后，保守党和自由民主党成立[[卡梅伦第一政府内阁|联合政府]]，亨特出任国家文化、奥运、媒体和体育大臣（领导[[英国文化部|英国文化部]]的同时兼任奥运大臣）。2010年5月13日被任命为[[枢密院顾问官|枢密院顾问官]]。<ref name="pc-13may2010">{{Cite web |url=http://www.privy-council.org.uk/files/other/13th%20May2010%20List.doc |title=Privy Council Orders 13 May 2010 |publisher=Privy Council |accessdate=2010-07-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611044054/http://www.privy-council.org.uk/files/other/13th%20May2010%20List.doc |archivedate=2011年6月11日 }}</ref>

亨特被英国《[[金融时报_(英国)|金融时报]]》称为“都市自由主义者”。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/e9dae3a4-83c2-11e8-96dd-fa565ec55929|title=Jeremy Hunt replaces Boris Johnson on the world stage|last=Mance|first=Henry|date=9 July 2018|work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]]|accessdate=17 July 2018|archive-date=2021-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113181806/https://www.ft.com/content/e9dae3a4-83c2-11e8-96dd-fa565ec55929|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 报销 ===
2009年，亨特受到{{le|国会标准委员会|Parliamentary Commissioner for Standards}}调查。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/mps-expenses/labour-mps-expenses/6780793/MPs-expenses-Jeremy-Hunt-to-repay-9500.html|title=MPs' expenses: Jeremy Hunt to repay £9,500|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=10 December 2009|accessdate=19 January 2011|location=London|archive-date=2019-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823001523/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/mps-expenses/labour-mps-expenses/6780793/MPs-expenses-Jeremy-Hunt-to-repay-9500.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="PC">{{cite web|title=Standards and Privileges Committee – Fourth Report Mr Jeremy Hunt|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200910/cmselect/cmstnprv/157/15702.htm|accessdate=4 January 2011|date=10 December 2009|publisher=Standards and Privilege Committee|archive-date=2018-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711121123/https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200910/cmselect/cmstnprv/157/15702.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>该委员会专员称：“亨特先生没有根据其代理人的生活实际开销而减少报销额外生活津贴，这违反了国会规则。因此，公共资金向选区代理人提供了利益...亨特从这一安排中没有收到真正的经济利益，错误是由于他对规则的误解造成的。”<ref name="PC" />

亨特提出偿还一半费用（9558.5英镑）的建议獲得接受。亨特还赔偿了他法姆纳姆的住宅1996英镑的费用，同时声称他哈默史密斯的住宅还在偿还抵押。专员说：“亨特先生爽快接受了错误的做法，违反了下议院的规则，在他法纳姆的家里提出公务开销和其他服务的报销，在这期间那里仍然是他主要的家。他已经偿还了报销的总额，共计1996英镑。显然，作为2005年5月的新科议员，他的办公室运作最多是无组织的。”报告没有显示其他问题。<ref name="leg">{{cite web|title=Review of past ACA payments|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200910/cmselect/cmmemest/348/348.pdf|accessdate=5 February 2010|date=4 February 2010|format=PDF|publisher=House of Commons Members Estimate Committee|page=86|archive-date=2010-02-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100214183244/http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200910/cmselect/cmmemest/348/348.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 脱欧观点 ===
2016年他支持[[英國脫歐公投|英国留欧]]，在脱欧派赢得公投后，亨特建议就未来的退出协议条款进行第二次公投，他支持英国留在[[單一市場|单一市场]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Jeremy Hunt suggests second EU referendum|trans_title=亨特呼吁第二次公投|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36647948|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|accessdate=2016-06-28|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204221001/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36647948|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/27/after-brexit-we-can-no-longer-ignore-fears-about-immigration/|work=The Daily Telegraph|title=We can win a better deal for Britain – it's the only way the EU can save itself|trans_title=我们为英国争取最好的交易-欧盟的存续只有一条路|last=Hunt|first=Jeremy|date=2016-06-27|accessdate=2017-01-18|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109032320/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/27/after-brexit-we-can-no-longer-ignore-fears-about-immigration/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年，他表示自己改变了主意，现在支持英国脱欧，理由是[[欧盟委员会|欧盟委员会]]在英国脱欧谈判中对英国政府的“傲慢态度”。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/oct/11/how-remain-voting-tories-responded-to-new-referendum-question|title=How remain-voting Tories responded to new referendum question|last=Weaver|first=Matthew|date=11 October 2017|work=The Guardian|accessdate=12 October 2017|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112012955/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/oct/11/how-remain-voting-tories-responded-to-new-referendum-question|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2018年7月，亨特表示担心英国可能会在未达成协议的情况下离开欧盟。他说，这将是“经济上难以置信的挑战”，并且“这将导致外交关系中的裂缝，这对我们多年来所拥有的伟大伙伴关系具有极大破坏性，这对维持国际秩序非常重要。”<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-no-deal-accident-scenario-eu-waits-uk-blink-jeremy-hunt-a8459881.html No-deal Brexit could happen 'by accident', Jeremy Hunt says] {{Wayback|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-no-deal-accident-scenario-eu-waits-uk-blink-jeremy-hunt-a8459881.html |date=20201109014334 }} ''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]''</ref>2018年12月接受《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》采访时，他暗示即使没有达成交易，英国也会“蓬勃发展”，尽管他继续支持[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]提出的英国脱欧协议。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Malnick|first1=Edward|title=Jeremy Hunt: UK will 'flourish and prosper' if it walks away from the EU without a deal|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/12/15/jeremy-hunt-uk-will-flourish-prosper-walks-away-eu-without-deal/|accessdate=23 December 2018|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=15 December 2018|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108113124/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/12/15/jeremy-hunt-uk-will-flourish-prosper-walks-away-eu-without-deal/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2019年3月，他表示需要“更多的努力”才能让国会议员支持梅的协议，但有“令人鼓舞的迹象”表明事情正在取得进展。<ref>{{cite web|title=Passing Brexit deal needs 'a lot more work'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-47607186|accessdate=5 June 2019|date=18 March 2019|work=BC News|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108001147/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-47607186|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 文化大臣 ==
[[File:Jeremy_Hunt_Farnham_2010_portrait.JPG|thumb]]
2010年9月，《旁观者》杂志的“raised eyebrows”报道了亨特的前{{le|国会秘书|Parliamentary secretary}}Naomi Gummer在亨特宣布文化部将裁员35%-50%后在文化部获得了一个合同制的公务员岗位。<ref name="obs">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/sep/19/jeremy-hunt-naomi-gummer-chadlington-dcms|work=[[The_Observer|The Observer]]|first=Jamie|last=Doward|title=Row after Tory peer's daughter is given job in culture secretary Jeremy Hunt's department|trans_title=保守党贵族的女儿获得了在亨特的部门的工作|date=2010-09-19|accessdate=2011-01-04|location=London|archive-date=2020-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706184424/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/sep/19/jeremy-hunt-naomi-gummer-chadlington-dcms|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{le|公务员工会|Public and Commercial Services Union}}组织的领袖质疑亨特的动机：“政治上独立的公务员是我国民主制度中根本性的一部分，我们将密切关注这是否被裙带关系和特权置于危险之中。”<ref name="obs" /> Gummer是保守党[[终身贵族|终身贵族]]、前保守党主管{{le|彼得·谷莫|Peter Gummer, Baron Chadlington}}的女儿。<ref name="obs" />

作为文化大臣，亨特计划并倡导将英国建设为欧洲宽带速度最快的国家。这个计划最开始被人们怀疑，因为这会导致[[英国电信|英国电信集团]]的垄断。<ref>{{cite news |last=Meyer |first=David |url=http://www.zdnet.com/broadband-policy-could-bring-back-bt-monopoly-claims-lords-report-7000001883/ |title=Broadband policy could bring back BT monopoly, claims Lords report |trans_title=宽带项目会让英国电信垄断，勋爵报告说 |publisher=[[ZDNet|ZDNet]] |date=2012-07-31 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2014-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129045911/http://www.zdnet.com/broadband-policy-could-bring-back-bt-monopoly-claims-lords-report-7000001883/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>亨特在任两年间，宽带速度的确增加了，但主要是由于更换了不同的包。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://media.ofcom.org.uk/2012/02/02/jump-in-uk-broadband-speeds/ |title=Jump in UK broadband speeds |trans_title=英国宽带速度的不稳定 |publisher=[[Ofcom|Ofcom]] |date=2012-02-02 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220180158/http://media.ofcom.org.uk/2012/02/02/jump-in-uk-broadband-speeds/ |archivedate=2013-12-20 }}</ref>他也推出了地方电视驱动政策，并使[[通讯管理局|通讯管理局]]颁发给地方电视台牌照，包括的地区有：贝尔法斯特、伯明翰、布莱顿和霍夫、布里斯托尔、加的夫、爱丁堡、格拉斯哥、格里姆斯比、利兹、利物浦、伦敦、曼彻斯特、纽卡斯尔、诺里奇、诺丁汉、牛津、普利茅斯、普利斯顿、谢菲尔德、南安普敦和斯旺西。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://consumers.ofcom.org.uk/2012/05/ofcom-invites-applications-for-first-21-local-tv-channels/ |title=Ofcom invites applications for first 21 local TV channels |trans_title=通管局批准了21个地方电视台的申请 |publisher=Ofcom |date=2012-05-10 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301030103/http://consumers.ofcom.org.uk/2012/05/ofcom-invites-applications-for-first-21-local-tv-channels/ |archivedate=2014-03-01 }}</ref>在文化政策方面，他的主要焦点是促进慈善事业，因为艺术和其他部门正在经历支出的削减。继承税的税额被减免成为促进艺术发展的措施。<ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=Alistair |url=http://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2011/03/george-osborne-announces-arts-philanthropy-measures-in-budget/ |title=George Osborne announces arts philanthropy measures in budget | News |trans_title=乔治·奥斯本宣布预算案中的慈善保护措施 |publisher=The Stage |date= |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2014-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207130850/http://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2011/03/george-osborne-announces-arts-philanthropy-measures-in-budget/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在亨特任内，与媒体和电信有关的竞争和政策问题成为文化大臣的职责范围；这些事务在商务大臣[[温斯·凯博|温斯·凯博]]向传媒大亨[[鲁伯特·默多克|鲁伯特·默多克]]宣战后被从凯博的手中移交到亨特手中。<ref name="cablerevs">{{cite news|last=Peston|first=Robert|title=What Vince Cable said about Rupert Murdoch and BSkyB|trans_title=温斯·凯博向默多克说了什么？|publisher=BBC News|date=2010-12-21|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/thereporters/robertpeston/2010/12/what_vince_cable_said_about_ru.html|accessdate=2012-04-24|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109032000/https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/thereporters/robertpeston/2010/12/what_vince_cable_said_about_ru.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 新闻集团案和列文森调查 ===
亨特被赋予了{{le|准司法权力|Quasi-judicial body}}，以便对[[新闻集团|新闻集团]]收购[[BSkyB|BSkyB]]进行裁决。亨特选择不向{{le|竞争委员会|Competition Commission}}提交这项交易，并在2011年3月3日宣布他打算接受新闻集团所作的一系列承诺，为交易达成铺平了道路。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/news-corp-bskyb-merger-update-march-2011|title=Culture Secretary Jeremy Hunt makes a statement on proposed merger|trans_title=文化大臣亨特就拟议的收购发表声明|publisher=[[Gov.uk|Gov.uk]]|date=2012-04-25|access-date=2017-02-08|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023535/https://www.gov.uk/government/news/news-corp-bskyb-merger-update-march-2011|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/notice-of-consultation-on-the-proposed-acquisition-by-news-corporation-of-up-to-60-9-of-bskyb-group-plc-march-2011|title=Notice of Consultation on the proposed acquisition by News Corporation of up to 60.9% of BSkyB Group PLC, March 2011|trans_title=有关新闻集团建议收购BSkyB集团最多60.9％股份的通知|publisher=Gov.uk|date=2011-03-03|access-date=2017-02-08|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112033108/https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/notice-of-consultation-on-the-proposed-acquisition-by-news-corporation-of-up-to-60-9-of-bskyb-group-plc-march-2011|dead-url=no}}</ref>在一系列[[世界新闻报电话窃听丑闻|电话黑客丑闻]]爆发后，[[英国下议院|下议院]]动议，呼吁新闻集团放弃投标。投标最终被放弃。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-14142307 |publisher=BBC News |title=News Corp withdraws bid for BSkyB |trans_title=新闻集团收购BSkyB |date=2011-07-13 |accessdate=2017-02-09 |archive-date=2011-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713201639/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-14142307 |dead-url=no }}</ref>据称亨特与新闻集团有不当联系。调查的主持者列文森法官收到了显示亨特的[[英国政府特别顾问|特别顾问]]亚当·史密斯与新闻集团公关主管及默多克的说客Frédéric Michel<ref>{{cite news|first=Helen|last=Pidd|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/apr/25/adam-smith-frederic-michel-correspondence|title=Adam Smith and Frédéric Michel: an intimate correspondence|trans_title=亚当·史密斯和弗雷德里克·米歇尔：私信|work=The Guardian|date=2012-04-25|accessdate=|archive-date=2020-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620072041/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2012/apr/25/adam-smith-frederic-michel-correspondence|dead-url=no}}</ref>详细往来的电子邮件。这引起了[[工党_(英国)|工党]]和其他反对者的不满并要求亨特辞职。<ref>{{cite news|first=Oliver|last=Wright|display-authors=etal|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/james-murdochs-revenge-evidence-that-shook-government-to-its-core-7675196.html|title=James Murdoch's revenge: Evidence that shook Government to its core|trans_title=詹姆斯·默多克的报复：证明这动摇了政府的核心|work=The Independent|date=2012-04-25|accessdate=2016-02-03|archive-date=2020-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200617012443/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/james-murdochs-revenge-evidence-that-shook-government-to-its-core-7675196.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>4月25日亨特的特别顾问史密斯辞职，<ref>{{cite news|first=Patrick|last=Wintour|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2012/apr/25/jeremy-hunt-adviser-adam-smith-quits|title=Jeremy Hunt's special adviser Adam Smith quits|trans_title=史密斯辞职|work=The Guardian|date=2012-04-25|accessdate=2016-02-03|archive-date=2021-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210123054501/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2012/apr/25/jeremy-hunt-adviser-adam-smith-quits|dead-url=no}}</ref>在此不久前，亨特发表了紧急议会声明，他说史密斯与米歇尔的联系是“显然不适当”的。亨特说列文森法官应该能够对指控进行调查和裁决，并请求尽可能早日向调查人员提供证据，澄清他自己。<ref>{{cite news|first=Robert|last=Winnett|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/leveson-inquiry/9226216/Jeremy-Hunt-admits-links-between-adviser-and-News-Corp-clearly-not-appropriate.html|title=Jeremy Hunt admits links between adviser and News Corp 'clearly not appropriate'|trans_title=杰里米·亨特承认顾问和新闻集团之间的联系显然不合适|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=2012-04-25|accessdate=2016-02-03|archive-date=2018-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713071525/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/leveson-inquiry/9226216/Jeremy-Hunt-admits-links-between-adviser-and-News-Corp-clearly-not-appropriate.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

亨特出席2012年5月31日的{{le|列文森调查|Leveson Inquiry}}之前，他与詹姆斯·鲁道夫的私人电子邮件通信出现在网络上。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.levesoninquiry.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Witness-List-28-31-May-2012.pdf|title=Leveson Inquiry Witness List Week Commencing 28 May 2012|trans_title=列文森调查5月28日开始传唤证人|publisher=The Leveson Inquiry|format=PDF|page=1|date=2012-05-25|access-date=2017-02-09|archive-date=2013-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602235707/http://www.levesoninquiry.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Witness-List-28-31-May-2012.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-18273297|title=Leveson Inquiry: Hunt defends 'congrats' Murdoch text|trans_title=列文森调查：亨特为给默多克的“贺信”辩护|publisher=BBC News|date=2012-05-31|accessdate=2012-05-31|archive-date=2021-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125020807/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-18273297|dead-url=no}}</ref>记者伊恩·马丁（Iain Martin）声称，在2010年默多克也参加的[[伦敦大学学院|伦敦大学学院]]大会上，他看到亨特藏在一棵树后面，以免被记者们看到：“我在聚会上四处寻找聚会组织者，发现文化大臣躲在一棵树后面，我知道他不愿在这种场合露面，怕被记者们看到。”<ref name="The night I saw Jeremy Hunt hide behind a tree before dinner with James Murdoch...">{{cite web|last1=Martin|first1=Iain|title=The night I saw Jeremy Hunt hide behind a tree before dinner with James Murdoch...|trans_title=我看见亨特躲在树后面，然后与詹姆斯·默多克共进晚餐去了……|url=http://capx.co/the-night-i-saw-jeremy-hunt-hide-behind-a-tree/|website=CapX|accessdate=2016-06-28|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112022141/https://capx.co/the-night-i-saw-jeremy-hunt-hide-behind-a-tree/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在听证会上，亨特这样说：“我想，那不是进行即兴采访的好时候，所以我移动到校园的另一边去……那里可能有也可能没有树！”<ref name="Hunt Leveson">{{cite news|title=Leveson Inquiry: 'I did not hide behind a tree', says Jeremy Hunt|trans_title=列文森调查：我没有躲在树后面，亨特说|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eoJ5B-wRq_c|website=[[YouTube|YouTube]]: [[Daily_Telegraph|Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=2016-06-28|archive-date=2020-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201222213135/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eoJ5B-wRq_c|dead-url=no}}</ref>

列文森法官明确亨特在报告发布是受到诸多误解，他申述道：“在某些方面，亨特对于这次并购的处理有值得称赞的地方。”<ref name="gov.uk">{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/270942/0780_iii.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309101724/https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/270942/0780_iii.pdf|archivedate=2014-03-09|title=An Inquiry Into The Culture, Practices And Ethics Of The Press|trans_title=一次关于媒体文化、实践和伦理的调查|last=Leveson|first=Brian|date=November 2012|volume=III|publisher=The Leveson Inquiry|format=PDF|pages=419, 422}}</ref>并总结说：“从对事件的仔细调查中，没有发现对亨特先生有实际偏见的可信证据。无论他公开还是私下对新闻集团或默多克父子说了什么，证据表明，他一接手处理这次收购，就真的渴望把这件事办好。他的行动是作为一个决策者去询问新闻集团的意见，他也表示愿意听取通信管理局对咨询的回复意见和推荐的程度而行动。”<ref name="gov.uk" />

=== 对足球流氓的评论 ===
2010年6月，亨特引起了争议，他认为[[足球流氓|足球流氓]]对[[希尔斯堡惨案|希尔斯堡惨案]]中96名球迷的死亡发挥了作用；当警力不足和球场围栏的错误设置被认定为惨案的主因后，亨特道歉说：“我知道球迷的愤怒在1989年4月的可怕事件没有起到任何作用，我向利物浦球迷和那些在希尔斯堡灾难中被杀害和伤害的家庭道歉，如果我的意见对他们造成任何伤害的话。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/merseyside/10434714.stm|title=Jeremy Hunt 'sorry' over Hillsborough hooligans claim|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=28 June 2010|date=28 June 2010}}</ref>
=== 税务 ===
2012年4月，《每日电讯报》透露，亨特通过以财产形式接收来自{{le|热门|Hotcourses}}公司的股息，并迅速将其租回公司，从而避税超过10万英镑。实物[[股息|股息]]是在股息税增加10％之前支付的，因而亨特不需要为这笔交易支付[[印花税|印花税]]。<ref name="hotprop">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/9232715/Jeremy-Hunt-avoided-100000-tax-bill-in-deal-just-days-before-rate-rise.html|title=Jeremy Hunt avoided £100,000 tax bill in deal just days before rate rise|first=Holly|last=Watt|first2=Claire|last2=Newell|work=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=27 April 2012|date=27 April 2012|location=London|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108112207/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/9232715/Jeremy-Hunt-avoided-100000-tax-bill-in-deal-just-days-before-rate-rise.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 2012伦敦奥运 ===
作为文化大臣，亨特是负责监督2012年奥运会和残奥会的政府大臣。当安保公司G4S声明无法提供足够的安保人手时，亨特请[[英国国防大臣|国防大臣]][[菲利普·哈蒙德|菲利普·哈蒙德]]部署英军士兵以填补人手上的空缺，亨特被迫“重新考虑”私人企业的可靠性。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2012/aug/14/g4s-advertises-staff-police-crimes?INTCMP=SRCH | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Alan | last=Travis | title=G4S advertises for staff to help police investigate crimes | trans_title=G4S称员工正在帮助警察调查犯罪 | date=2012-08-14 | accessdate=2017-02-10 | archive-date=2019-06-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604005805/https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2012/aug/14/g4s-advertises-staff-police-crimes?INTCMP=SRCH | dead-url=no }}</ref>亨特决定由[[丹尼·博伊尔|丹尼·博伊尔]]导演的奥运会开幕式预算增加一倍，整次奥运会都被国际上认为是巨大的成功。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/jan/06/2012-olympics-britain-party|title=Banging Olympic drum for Britain to cost £39m but 'it's not a party'|trans_title=喧闹的奥运会耗资3900万英镑|work=The Guardian|date=2012-01-06|last=Gibson|first=Owen|accessdate=2017-02-10|archive-date=2019-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626182956/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/jan/06/2012-olympics-britain-party|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Alexandra |last=Topping |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/aug/13/london-2012-games-verdict-around-world |title=London 2012: verdict from around the world | Sport |trans_title=伦敦2012，世界评价 |work=The Guardian |date=2012-08-13 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111214235/http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/aug/13/london-2012-games-verdict-around-world |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Tom |last=Lawrence |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/global-praise-for-superb-london-2012-olympics-8037820.html |title=Global praise for 'superb' London 2012 Olympics – Home News – UK |trans_title=2012年伦敦奥运会的全球赞誉 |work=The Independent |date=2012-08-13 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2018-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627210559/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/global-praise-for-superb-london-2012-olympics-8037820.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2013/apr/09/bafta-tv-awards-nominations-olympics|title=Bafta TV nominations: BBC London 2012 Olympics coverage gets hat-trick|trans_title=Bafta电视提名：BBC伦敦2012奥运会覆盖率的帽子戏法|work=The Guardian|date=2013-04-09|accessdate=2016-02-24|archive-date=2019-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604162918/https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2013/apr/09/bafta-tv-awards-nominations-olympics|dead-url=no}}</ref>博伊尔后来说，政府原来打算砍掉开幕式中[[国民保健署_(英国)|全国卫生服务]]的那一部分，但亨特力排众议，保住了那一部分。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/10/london-olympic-opening-ceremony-team-was-put-under-political-pre/ |title=London Olympic opening ceremony team was 'put under political pressure to remove section about the NHS' |trans_title=伦敦奥运会开幕式团队遇到的政治压力：政府要求删除全国卫生服务的那一部分 |newspaper=Telegraph |first=Lydia |last=Willgress |date=2016-07-10 |accessdate=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125161300/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/10/london-olympic-opening-ceremony-team-was-put-under-political-pre/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

奥运会赢得了广泛的赞誉，志愿者、英国军方和公众的热情被特别高度赞扬。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-19233495|work=BBC News|title=London 2012: IOC chief Jaques Rogge 'very happy' with Games|trans_title=国际奥林匹克委员会主席“非常开心”|date=2012-08-12|accessdate=2012-08-14|archive-date=2012-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120813101505/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-19233495|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/aug/12/has-olympics-changed-london-2012|title=Has the Olympics changed London?|trans_title=奥运会改变了伦敦？|work=The Guardian|date=2012-08-12|accessdate=2012-08-14|first=Hannah|last=Waldram|archive-date=2013-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113193544/http://www.theguardian.com/sport/london-2012-olympics-blog/2012/aug/12/has-olympics-changed-london-2012|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Scanlan|first=Wayne|date=2012-08-10|url=http://www.calgaryherald.com/sports/2012-summer-games/Buoyed+record+medal+haul+suprisingly+sunny/7072134/story.html|title=Buoyed by a record medal haul – and surprisingly sunny skies – the British have embraced the Olympics, turning out to live sites in droves to cheer on Team GB|trans_title=奖牌和令人惊讶的晴朗天空 - 英国人已经接受了奥运会，转向了直播网站，以鼓舞英国代表队|work=[[Calgary_Herald|Calgary Herald]]|accessdate=2012-08-14|archive-date=2012-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120816063024/http://www.calgaryherald.com/sports/2012-summer-games/Buoyed+record+medal+haul+suprisingly+sunny/7072134/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>此后，亨特将学校运动会设为奥运遗产项目。虽然在削减学校体育预算时有批评声，<ref>{{cite news |first=Denis |last=Campbell |url=https://www.theguardian.com/education/2012/aug/06/michael-gove-own-goal-school-sports |title=Michael Gove's political own goal on school sports | Education |trans_title=迈克尔·戈夫的政治目标定在学校体育上 |work=The Guardian |date=2012-08-06 |accessdate=2015-07-27 |archive-date=2021-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120014029/https://www.theguardian.com/education/2012/aug/06/michael-gove-own-goal-school-sports |dead-url=no }}</ref>11953所学校在第一年参加了学校运动会。<ref>{{cite web |page=1|url=http://www.culture.gov.uk/images/publications/School-Games-Regional-Breakdown-Map.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120609200442/http://culture.gov.uk/images/publications/School-Games-Regional-Breakdown-Map.pdf|archivedate=2012-06-09|format=PDF|title=School Games Regional Breakdown|trans_title=学校运动区域性崩溃|publisher=Gov.uk}}</ref>亨特还致力于增加对旅游业重要性的重视，特别是[[中华人民共和国旅游业|中国旅游]]市场的潜力。<ref>{{cite news|first=Nicholas|last=Cecil|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/culture-secretary-jeremy-hunt-fasttracks-chinese-visas-to-lure-tourists-8045867.html|title=Culture Secretary Jeremy Hunt fast-tracks Chinese visas to lure tourists|work=[[London_Evening_Standard|London Evening Standard]]|date=14 August 2012|accessdate=27 July 2015|archive-date=2014-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112195953/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/culture-secretary-jeremy-hunt-fasttracks-chinese-visas-to-lure-tourists-8045867.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 卫生大臣 ==
{{overly detailed|section|date=July 2018}}2012年9月4日[[内阁改组|内阁改组]]，亨特接替[[安德鲁·兰斯利|安德鲁·兰斯利]]任[[卫生大臣|卫生大臣]]。<ref name="reshuffle 2012">{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-19472688 | publisher=BBC News | title=Cabinet reshuffle: Lansley replaced by Hunt in health job | trans_title=内阁改组：亨特接替兰斯利 | date=2012-09-04 | accessdate=2017-02-10 | archive-date=2020-11-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125063005/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-19472688 | dead-url=no }}</ref>亨特说这个任命是“我一生中的一个大任务和最大荣幸”。[[英国医学会|英国医学会]]主席{{le|马克·波特|Mark Porter (anaesthetist)}}博士说：“新卫生大臣的任命对医生和政府共同改善病人护理工作和应对全国卫生服务带来的诸多挑战来说是一个新机遇。”<ref name="pulse reshuffle">{{cite news|url=http://www.pulsetoday.co.uk/lansley-replaced-by-hunt-as-health-secretary-in-cabinet-reshuffle/14540746.fullarticle|title=Loading|trans_title=内阁改组中亨特成为卫生大臣|publisher=Pulse Today|date=2012-09-04|last=Collins|first=Gemma|accessdate=2015-07-27|archive-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609153103/http://www.pulsetoday.co.uk/lansley-replaced-by-hunt-as-health-secretary-in-cabinet-reshuffle/14540746.fullarticle|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[英国医学会|英国医学会]]的副主席说：“亨特成为新的卫生大臣是国民卫生服务的灾难，我担心这个更激烈的右翼会追随私有化的议程。”亨特曾与人合著一本关于国民卫生服务的书，其中提到“（国民卫生服务）应该被一个新的卫生保健制度所取代，人们将钱付给私人卫生账户，然后他们可以购买公共和私人提供者的护理服务。那些没有足够储蓄的人将由国家资助。”<ref name="toby">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2009/aug/16/tory-mps-back-nhs-dismantling|title=Key Tory MPs backed call to dismantle NHS|work=The Guardian|first=Toby|last=Helm|first2=Rajeev|last2=Syal|date=16 August 2009|accessdate=31 January 2014|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309170114/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2009/aug/16/tory-mps-back-nhs-dismantling|dead-url=no}}</ref>

《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》的科技记者Tom Chivers表示关注亨特对[[顺势疗法|顺势疗法]]的支持，<ref>{{cite news|work=The Daily Telegraph|url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/tomchiversscience/100179258/jeremy-hunt-health-secretary-thinks-homeopathy-works/|title=Jeremy Hunt, Health Secretary, thinks homeopathy works|location=London|date=4 September 2012|last=Chiver|first=Tom|accessdate=2019-07-04|archive-date=2016-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328194756/http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/tomchiversscience/100179258/jeremy-hunt-health-secretary-thinks-homeopathy-works/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>同家报社的医疗主编Rebecca Smith说：“卫生大臣亨特因其对堕胎和顺势疗法的看法而成为一个有争议的人物。”2014年亨特请卫生部{{le|首席医疗官|Chief Medical Officer (United Kingdom)}}主持一个对法国医疗制造商[[布瓦宏|布瓦宏]]开发的三次顺势疗法药品的专家评估。<ref name="guardian-20140508">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/may/08/jeremy-hunt-homeopathy-studies-chief-medical-officer|title=Jeremy Hunt sent homeopathy studies to chief medical officer|first=Sarah|last=Boseley|first2=Rowena|last2=Mason|work=The Guardian|date=8 May 2014|accessdate=6 October 2015|archive-date=2016-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221135751/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/may/08/jeremy-hunt-homeopathy-studies-chief-medical-officer|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而，2014年9月在伦敦广播公司的一次电台采访中，亨特否认自己是顺势疗法的支持者，并反思他从前作为一个新国会议员时缺乏经验而签署了支持顺势疗法的议案。但是他还是支持在医生推荐的情况下由国民卫生服务给顺势疗法提供资金。<ref>{{cite web|title=Jeremy Hunt: Live On LBC|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y96OrC4kCc8|accessdate=26 September 2016|date=10 September 2014|publisher=[[LBC|LBC]] (YouTube)|archive-date=2019-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710093255/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y96OrC4kCc8&gl=US&hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2012年10月的《[[泰晤士报|泰晤士报]]》采访中，亨特说他赞成将[[堕胎|堕胎]]限制从24周减少到12周。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-19854465|title=Abortion limit reduction favoured by Jeremy Hunt|publisher=BBC News|date=6 October 2012|accessdate=8 December 2012|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309104301/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-19854465|dead-url=no}}</ref>2013年，他表示全英国过早死亡的地区差异令人震惊。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-22844227|publisher=BBC News|date=11 June 2013|first=James|last=Gallagher|title=Early deaths: Regional variations 'shocking' – Hunt|accessdate=2019-07-04|archive-date=2020-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820140011/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-22844227|dead-url=no}}</ref>

